  "response_text": "The commercial begins in a muted, almost black-and-white close view of two people leaning over something together. On the left is an older man, partly in shadow, seen in profile. Beside him is a young adult woman with light hair worn loose, looking downward with a focused, neutral expression. Both appear to be examining an item just below the bottom edge of view.\n\nThe item is then shown clearly in someone’s hands: a bright pink Wizard package, now in color. The rectangular package has a large “Wizard” logo across the upper front, a yellow “NEW” label in the top corner, and “Crystal Air” printed near the bottom. The package artwork is dominated by pink flowers and a circular, rose-colored disc with raised, wavy swirl patterns. Pale hands hold the package at both sides, tilting it slightly so the front is easy to see.\n\nThe young woman reappears in warm indoor light, now in color, holding the opened pink glass-like disc close to her nose as if smelling it. She has long light-brown hair and wears a dark jacket. Other people in casual clothing are partly visible behind her, out of focus, including someone in a yellow or orange top. She smiles subtly, seeming pleased. Small white text appears along the bottom: “Among leading national brands.”\n\nA hand then carries the round pink Crystal Air disc toward a sunlit windowsill. The disc is translucent and circular, with raised pale wavy lines across its face, like ripples. The hand sets it upright on the sill in front of a window. White safety text at the bottom reads, “Please read and follow all package directions.” The room is bright, with daylight coming through the window and a soft pink glow reflecting from the product.\n\nThe disc remains standing on the windowsill while people move in the room behind it, blurred through the window area. One person in a teal top and dark jacket passes or sits in the background, while another person in blue jeans stands nearby. The product stays in the foreground, small but distinct, its pink circular face facing outward.\n\nWhite text appears over the scene: “4 weeks later.” After this, the young woman is shown seated near the same window, smiling broadly while holding a telephone handset to her ear. She appears relaxed and cheerful, with her knees drawn up as she talks. The windowsill remains behind her in soft light, suggesting the product has stayed in place over time.\n\nThe scene returns to the empty sunlit windowsill. The pink Crystal Air disc is visible again, glowing warmly near the window, still upright with its wavy pattern clearly visible. The final product display shows the pink disc in the foreground beside several Wizard Crystal Air packages arranged behind it. The packages come in different colors, including pink, green, and purple, indicating different fragrance varieties. The “Wizard” name is large on the boxes, and the pink package again carries a “NEW” label. A large Wizard logo graphic appears over the display at the end, reinforcing the brand name while the pink, green, and purple discs and boxes remain grouped on the windowsill.",
